\ss{Examples}

Here are some examples of proving stuff!

\begin{example}
    Prove that

    \begin{equation}
        A \implies \lnot \parens{\lnot A}
    \end{equation}

    Substitute $\lnot x \Longrightarrow x \to \bot$.

    \begin{alignedmath}
        A \implies \lnot \parens{A \to \bot} \\
        A \implies \parens{\parens{A \implies \bot} \implies \bot} \\
        A \implies \parens{A \implies \bot} \implies \bot \\
    \end{alignedmath}

    The proof of this is then

    \begin{equation}
        \fn{x,f}{\eva{f}{x}}
    \end{equation}
\end{example}

\begin{example}
    Prove that

    \begin{equation}
        \lnot \parens{\lnot A} \notimplies A
    \end{equation}

    Rather, I am proving that

    \begin{equation}
        \lnot \parens{\lnot \parens{\lnot A} \implies A}
    \end{equation}

    Which is equivalent to 

    \begin{equation}
        \parens{\parens{\parens{A \implies \bot} \implies \bot} \implies A} \implies \bot
    \end{equation}

\end{example}